Save The individual elements (product, inspection, exposure, area, reference, contour) must be saved separately. The individual elements are not saved automatically. Saving the product is certainly useful; inspections, areas etc. can, but do not have to be saved separately, as they are contained in the product. Similar elements can be saved and loaded again separately so that the entire set of parameters does not always have to be recreated when dealing with similar workpiece types. This is made possible by the fact that a product always contains the associated inspections and areas (see Application structure
).

